e a key strategy in ending the horrible disease when it was finally contained in India. In House on Fire, William H. Foege describes his own experiences in public health and details the remarkable program that involved people from countries around the world in pursuit of a single objective—eliminating smallpox forever. Rich with the details of everyday life, as well as a few adventures, House on Fire gives an intimate sense of what it is like to work on the ground in some of the world’s most impoverished countries—and tells what it is like to contribute to programs that really do change the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aInternational cooperation. 0aPhysiciansvBiography. 0aPublic health personnelvBiography. 0aSmallpoxxHistoryy20th century. 0aSmallpox. 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh  ablended family.  acollege party.  acoming of age.  adangers of drunk driving.  adead daughter.  adont drink and drive.  adrama.  adrunk driving accident.  afamily saga.  afamily.  amanslaughter.  aromance.  ashocking conclusion.  athriller novel.  atight plot.  atragedy.  atroublemaker.  awarning story.  ayoung adult.1 aHooker Odom, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJ. Sencer, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aL. Milbank, Samuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026836440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094889140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948891423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948891/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  